  This paper deals with the following fractional Schr$ \ddot{\textrm{o}}$dinger
equations with Choquard-type nonlinearities \begin{equation*}
\left\{\begin{array}{r@{\ \ }c@{\ \ }ll}
  (-\Delta)^{\frac{\alpha}{2}}u + u - C_{n,-\beta} \,(|x|^{\beta-n}\ast
u^{p})\, u^{p-1}& = &0 & \mbox{in}\ \ \mathbb{R}^{n}\,, \\[0.05cm]
  u & > & 0 & \mbox{on}\ \ \mathbb{R}^{n}, \end{array}\right. \end{equation*}
where $ 0< \alpha,\beta < 2, 1\leq p <\infty \,\,and\,\, n\geq 2. $ First we
construct a decay result at infinity and a narrow region principle for related
equations. Then we establish the radial symmetry of positive solutions for the
above equation with the generalized direct method of moving planes.
